    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="421" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                <head>No. 420.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Romero</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 16,
                                    1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 7th instant, in relation to the Apache
                            Indians, who, it is represented, have been leaving the San Carlos
                            Reservation in Arizona Territory and invading Sonora, Mexico.</p>
                <p>I have accordingly submitted copy of your note to the Secretaries of War
                            and of the Interior, who have been asked to adopt such further measures
                            as may be found practicable by their respective Departments for the
                            suppression of the abuses complained of.</p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
